    "long_instructions": "#### Assessment\r\n\r\nCreate a song with 3 parts using the prechorus and chorus tracks from Katy Perry's Fireworks.\r\n\r\nEach part of your song should include a <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-boombox\" style=\"color: #58BEF9; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Bass </span>, <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-guitars\" style=\"color: #64D25A; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Lead </span>, and <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone-stand\" style=\"color: #F99258; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Vocal </span> track. You can decide which ones to use from the song itself!\r\n\r\nTry listening to the example song to hear what this could sound like!\r\n\r\nThis is an **Assessment** level, which means it covers the key parts of this lesson. Press the <i class=\"fa-clipboard-list fa-solid\"></i> Rubric button to see what it takes to fully complete this level!\r\n\r\nWhen you've finished the level, press the **Submit** button below! After you submit:\r\n- You won't be able to edit your code! If you need to make a change, you can press Unsubmit to make your edits and then submit again\r\n- Your teacher will be able to give you a score and feedback on your work",
